Earthquake seismograph (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Managua - A 5.4-magnitude earthquake jolted Nicaragua on Wednesday, killing a woman and damaging homes close the epicenter in the country's north, officials said.The quake struck at 10:48 in the area between the El Hoyo and Momotombo volcanoes, at a shallow depth of 2.9km. The woman, Higinia Margarita Cruz, suffered a heart attack from the shock of the shaking, said First Lady Rosario Murillo, who is also the government spokesperson. Cruz was 78.Windows shattered in a building under construction in Puerto Momotombo and many homes sustained damage to roofs.Startled locals ran outside their homes and stayed there, concerned that if they went inside, another quake might strike.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.